But you are looking for distinct 2D points, a 2D point is defined by x, y coordinates. So point-0 is x[0] and y[0], point-1 x[1] and y[1] etc..
So going by this you would need to first find your points, then compare their respective coordinates.

(not optimised) An approach would be to first find matching x coordinates, then check if y also matches if so, then this is your none distinct point.
